## Hints for Future Agents
- The RLS policy structure is now: each branch is independently auth'd,
  so adding new chat scopes (e.g. spectator-vs-team) means adding a 4th
  OR branch, not refactoring the existing three.
- 8s timeout chosen empirically: post_message is normally <1s; 8s catches
  realistic prod hangs without false-positiving on slow networks.

## Codebase Discoveries
- `room_messages_insert` policy ordering matters: spectator branch came
  BEFORE team branch in the old version, which is why team-scoped
  spectator inserts were slipping through (then SELECT readback failing
  and hanging the client).

